Tags: ['Експорт', 'Мінагро', 'Польща', 'Зерно', 'Сольський']

Type: Article

<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/yкринформ/2023-04-05T-41-06-56-03-00/630_360_1655714911-861.jpg)Ukraine would reduce the volume of transportation of grain by road through Europe if Russia ceases to block the work of Ukrainian seaports.

The Minister of Agrarian Policy and Food of Ukraine Mykolasolsky said this, Ukrinform reports with reference to [](https://minagro.gov.ua/news/mikola-solskij-na-vartist-zerna-u-sviti-vplivaye-vijna-proti-ukrayini)He noted that if the whole world community managed to squeeze Russia to increase inspections in Bosphorus, Ukraine could send several times more grain vessels per day. Accordingly, the flow of car transportation of Ukrainian grain in Europe could be reduced.

According to Solsky, exports are cheaper for the Ukrainian farmer, and therefore more profitable.

He stressed that Russia continues to artificially restrain the export of Ukrainian [](https://www.ukrinform.ua/tag-zerno)by the sea, inhibiting the inspection of the Vuden in the Bosphorus. Only 2-3 ships are inspected. The minister explained that Ukrainian ports did not work at full capacity due to military aggression. Therefore, for the export of Ukrainian grain, we have to look for alternatives, including through Poland.

